--- Q5: replace-all with a GROWING replacement — is new_line shift-aware? ---
  ground truth: EXPANDME at old lines [2,4,6], each -> 3 lines (+2 per site)
  => new_line [2,6,10] means SHIFT-AWARE (post-edit lines)
  => new_line [2,4,6] means it MIRRORS old_line (pre-edit lines; client must accumulate)
  [completed] path=expand.txt details length=3
      details old_line values: [2,6,10]  (expected [2,4,6])
      details new_line values: [2,6,10]
      VERDICT: SHIFT-AWARE — new_line is a real post-edit line
        details[0] VERBATIM: {"old_string":"EXPANDME","old_line":2,"new_string":"alpha inserted line\nbravo inserted line\ncharlie inserted line","new_line":2,"context_before":"header of expand.txt\n","context_after":"filler 1\nalpha inserted line\nbravo inserted line\n","line_prefix":""}
